block.rsgauges.industrial_block_detector:
§6A switch emitting a redstone signal if one or more blocks in front if it match a configured type or category.§r
The configuration is set using buttons at the opposite side of the detector and encompass the 'range' (observing how far), the 'threshold' (how many blocks have to match), the 'filter' (criteria, e.g. solid, fluid, wood log, ores, plants, crops, mature crops, and other ore dictionary based filters), the 'debouncing' (anti-jitter delay), and the output 'power' (at all sides except the detector side). Note: The detector recognises modded blocks only if they are correctly registered in the ore dictionary (you need to test it). §r
